{{Infobox magazine | title = Milwaukee Magazine | logo = | logo_size = | image_file = <!-- cover.jpg (omit the "file: prefix --> | image_size = <!-- (defaults to user thumbnail size if no size is stated) --> | image_alt = | image_caption = | editor = | editor_title = | previous_editor = | staff_writer = | photographer = | category = City magazine | frequency = Monthly | circulation = | publisher = | founder = | founded = 1983 | firstdate = <!-- {{Start date|year|month|day}} --> | company = [[Quad/Graphics]] | country = [[United States]] | based = [[Milwaukee]], [[Wisconsin]] | language = English | website = {{URL|http://www.milwaukeemag.com}} | issn = 0741-1243 | oclc = }}
'''''Milwaukee Magazine''''' is a monthly city magazine serving the [[Milwaukee metropolitan area]] in [[Wisconsin]], [[United States]]. It bills itself as "Southeastern Wisconsin's most authoritative source for Events and Dining," and reports a readership of 200,000.
==History and profile== A magazine named ''Milwaukee'' (sometimes ''Milwaukee, the metropolitan magazine'') was established in 1977 ({{ISSN|0746-3790}}), and its final edition (volume 8, issue 4) was published in May 1983.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://libus.csd.mu.edu/search~S1/t?Milwaukee+%28Milwaukee%2C+Wis.+%3A+1977%29|title = Milwaukee|accessdate = 26 January 2017|year = 2017|publisher = [[Marquette University]]|website = Marquette University Libraries Online Catalog}}</ref> It was continued by ''Milwaukee Magazine'' ({{ISSN|0741-1243}}), which designated its first edition, published in June 1983, as volume 8, issue 5.<ref>{{cite web|title = Milwaukee magazine|year = 2017|url = http://libus.csd.mu.edu/search~S1?/tMilwaukee+magazine/tmilwaukee+magazine/1%2C2%2C4%2CB/frameset&FF=tmilwaukee+magazine&2%2C%2C3|website = Marquette University Libraries Online Catalog|publisher = [[Marquette University]]|accessdate = 26 January 2017}}</ref><ref name=crma>{{cite web|title=Milwaukee Magazine|url=http://www.citymag.org/City-and-Regional-Magazine-Association/CRMA-Membership/Member-Directory/index.php/name/Milwaukee-Magazine/listing/24672/|work=CRMA|accessdate=22 November 2015}}</ref> Its office is located in the [[Historic Third Ward]] neighborhood of downtown [[Milwaukee]]. It is printed by its parent company, [[Quad/Graphics]], and is a member of the [[City and Regional Magazine Association]] (CRMA).<ref name=crma/> The magazine is the recipient of various awards for its design and editorials.<ref name=crma/>
